additional_house_rules:

- No unreasonably loud music.
- No photos shoots or video shoots or other professional activities of any kind.
- No parties. Violating this will result in a penalty charge.
- No more than 2 visitors at a time.
- No visitors/unauthorized guests allowed before 8am and after 8pm. If this is violated, there will be a penalty charge of double the nightly room rate.
- We do not allow anything (bikes, etc.) to be attached/locked to the front yard fences, posts, etc.
- No bicycles nor oversized items inside the apartment.
- Both bedrooms will be available when booking with over 2 guests. Only the larger bedroom and full-size sofa pull out will be available when booking with 1 or 2 guests.
- At least one guest must be 21 years old or older.
- Reservation must include all guests. No exceptions.
- We do require photo ID at check-in and it must match the reservation name.
description:
The Quincy Light House is an amazing getaway place when you want to visit New York in style and comfort. Impeccably maintained, this retreat is situated in the historic neighborhood of Bedford-Stuyvesant on a quiet tree-lined block.

Convenient access to public transportation includes walking distance to the J/M/Z and A/C subway lines. The B46 and B52 buses, which you can catch half a block away, can take you to L and G subway lines as well as to Williamsburg and Downtown Brooklyn.

This is a full 2 bedroom space that sleeps up to 5 comfortably. Both bedrooms have queen beds and there's an additional pull out full-size sofa bed in the living room.
Upon ascending the beautiful staircase, the open-layout kitchen and living room welcomes you.

Guests are welcomed to use the kitchen and there are many take-out/delivery options nearby.

TBD

Many options for dining and social activities nearby. The Brooklyn Museum, Brooklyn Botanical Gardens and Prospect Park are just a cab ride away.

Plenty of public transportation options available. Convenient car access to Manhattan, Queens, and Long Island.
